1
00:00:00,006 --> 00:00:06,750
PR 59 adds auto-discovery flags to lxa
board scan. Let's see them in action.

2
00:00:14,428 --> 00:00:19,684
The --user and --org flags auto-discover
repos without manual configuration.

3
00:00:20,293 --> 00:00:22,981
Let's create a new project board.

4
00:00:33,531 --> 00:00:37,035
The board is created with workflow columns
ready.

5
00:00:37,643 --> 00:00:42,875
Now the magic: scan with --user to
auto-discover all repos with activity.

6
00:00:58,590 --> 00:01:04,230
Without specifying any repositories, it
found and added items automatically.

7
00:01:04,845 --> 00:01:10,221
PR 59 also adds Gist-based config sync for
ephemeral environments.

8
00:01:18,184 --> 00:01:22,072
Config persists across sessions via GitHub
Gist.

9
00:01:22,404 --> 00:01:26,508
Let's view the board on GitHub to see our
auto-discovered items.

10
00:01:36,305 --> 00:01:43,385
Here's our board in kanban view. On the
left we see Icebox and Backlog columns
with open issues.

11
00:01:48,699 --> 00:01:54,435
Scrolling right we see Agent Coding and
Human Review columns for items needing
attention.

12
00:01:59,746 --> 00:02:05,866
And here are Final Review, Approved, Done,
and Closed columns tracking the full
workflow.

13
00:02:10,179 --> 00:02:14,691
Each item was auto-discovered and placed
based on its GitHub state.

